                            <comment id="16529308" author="daniel_sun" created="Mon, 2 Jul 2018 01:17:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The cache is especially useful for collection types, which are widely and frequently used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wish `clearParameterizedTypeCache` would be useful for you to resolve IDE issues caused by the stale cache items, see&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/pull/765&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/pull/765&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16530660" author="daniel_sun" created="Tue, 3 Jul 2018 01:31:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In addition, you can enable/disable the parameterized type cache by setting system property &quot;groovy.enable.parameterized.type.cache&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
